      "writtenOn": "2020-09-22T14:54:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "caveat: stacked CLs.\nCQ/BQ data will reference only top-most CL on which was triggered, omitting all Cls it depended on and which were available to the `analyze` step. Hence, you\u0027ll feed incomplete info the algo.\n\nI think this will make algorithm appear less safe than it actually be in practice.\n\nI don\u0027t know how frequently CL stacks are CQed, so I don\u0027t know how big this effect would be.\n\nAnyhow, i think it\u0027s fine to start as is and fetch full list at a later time based on Output GitilesCommit (or got_revision) + gitiles DIFF (or maybe querying logdog for git diff step output?)).",
      "revId": "64c91198af6f0e6369a2299bb15b9fdac30a6adf",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
